<%# Locals: home_path.
    logo-sm/logo-lg spans — app.min.css's collapsed/mobile states drive visibility off these two
    class names specifically (`body[data-sidebar-size=sm] .logo span.logo-lg{display:none}` /
    `span.logo-sm{display:block}`, plus an equivalent mobile-width rule): logo-sm is the collapsed
    sidebar's mark (BRAND_LOGO_CIRCLE_URL), logo-lg the expanded sidebar's full wordmark
    (BRAND_LOGO_MAIN_URL) — the two-span structure itself is load-bearing, not decorative: a
    single image with no collapsed variant doesn't hide/shrink at all when the sidebar collapses,
    and visibly overlaps the topbar's hamburger button (caught after fixing the collapse toggle
    itself actually reaching a visibly collapsed state for the first time — see
    sidebar_controller.js). %>
<%= link_to home_path, class: "logo brand-text d-flex align-items-center h-100 ps-2" do %>
  <span class="logo-sm"><%= tag.img src: ApplicationHelper::BRAND_LOGO_CIRCLE_URL, alt: "xEvent", height: 32, width: 32 %></span>
  <span class="logo-lg"><%= tag.img src: ApplicationHelper::BRAND_LOGO_MAIN_URL, alt: "xEvent", height: 28 %></span>
<% end %>
